cancelOrder((address,address,address,add.details: After calling, the order can not be filled anymore.      Throws if order is invalid or sender does not have permission to cancel.

params.order: Order to cancel. Order must be OrderStatus.FILLABLE.

cancelOrdersUpTo(uint256).details: Cancels all orders created by makerAddress with a salt less than or equal to the targetOrderEpoch      and senderAddress equal to msg.sender (or null address if msg.sender == makerAddress).

params.targetOrderEpoch: Orders created with a salt less or equal to this value will be cancelled.

executeTransaction(uint256,address,bytes.details: Executes an exchange method call in the context of signer.

params.salt: Arbitrary number to ensure uniqueness of transaction hash.
params.signature: Proof of signer transaction by signer.
Proof that order has been created by maker.
params.takerAssetFillAmount: Desired amount of takerAsset to sell.

fillOrder((address,address,address,addre.return: Amounts filled and fees paid by maker and taker.

getAssetProxy(bytes4).return: The asset proxy registered to assetProxyId. Returns 0x0 if no proxy is registered.

getOrderInfo((address,address,address,ad.details: Gets information about an order: status, hash, and amount filled.

isValidSignature(bytes32,address,bytes).details: Verifies that a signature is valid.

preSign(bytes32,address,bytes).details: Approves a hash on-chain using any valid signature type.      After presigning a hash, the preSign signature type will become valid for that hash and signer.

params.signature: Proof that the hash has been signed by signer.
params.signerAddress: Address that should have signed the given hash.

registerAssetProxy(address).details: Registers an asset proxy to its asset proxy id.      Once an asset proxy is registered, it cannot be unregistered.

params.assetProxy: Address of new asset proxy to register.

setSignatureValidatorApproval(address,bo.details: Approves/unnapproves a Validator contract to verify signatures on signer's behalf.

params.approval: Approval or disapproval of  Validator contract.
